			<h3 ><a href="#p15510"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=15510&amp;sid=4af85a60d89537be09274c45072d2d5e#p15510"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1206&amp;sid=4af85a60d89537be09274c45072d2d5e">IndyGuy</a></strong> &raquo; September 8th, 2006, 2:53 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">I'm pretty sure dogs and cats shed much worse than humans.  The extra shedding puts alot of extra strain on the brush motor.  I'll bet burned out brush motors are the leading cause of death in Roombas.</div>

			<div id="sig15510" class="signature">One Roomba to Rule Them ALL,
<br />One Scooba to do ALL the Mopping</div>

