			<h3 ><a href="#p15513"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=15513&amp;sid=4af85a60d89537be09274c45072d2d5e#p15513"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2267&amp;sid=4af85a60d89537be09274c45072d2d5e">Lin</a></strong> &raquo; September 8th, 2006, 3:54 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">I just bought my roomba in July, and specifically for my pets. I was tired of vacuuming every 2 days to keep pet hair at a minimum. Now I run my scheduler daily and my house always looks clean. I have 4 cats, 2 dogs, 2 horses, and rats.</div>

			<div id="sig15513" class="signature">4 cats + 2 dogs + 2 horses + 2 rats - roomba = Pet hair free house!</div>

		</div>

		
